// demo_fsm_tester — CLIENT-side .art for driving the DemoFsm gen_statem FC
// standalone with artheia.probe.
//
// DemoFsm (the statem node) takes NO external messages by design; its only
// TIPC-reachable surface is DemoFsmGate (receiver on DemoFsmIn), which
// post_event()s each event into the FSM in-process (the sm split pattern).
// To TEST the FSM we need a node DEFINITION carrying a `sender` on DemoFsmIn
// so the probe can bind a tester identity and cast DemoStart/DemoFinish/
// DemoReset at the gate — ordered, over one persistent connection.
//
// This node is NOT deployed (no composition / cluster). It exists only so
// `artheia.probe` can materialize a Python client straight from the model —
// same idiom as tools/tdb/system/tdb.art. See feedback-clients-via-art-probe.
//
// NOTE: like every cross-importing .art, this resolves ONLY through the
// canonical `system/` tree path (system/demo_test/… → symlink here), where the
// import dir-climb mirrors the package FQN. Parsing it at the physical path
// fails the `import system.demo.*` resolution — expected, not a bug; the probe
// always loads it through `system/demo_test/`.

package system.demo_test

// Pull the real DemoFsm messages + interfaces + the gate node into scope.
import system.demo.*

// ---- extern peer (materialized from the import) --------------------------
//
// `extern` = forward-decl: the real DemoFsmGate (tipc 0xd0010007 + its
// `receiver events requires DemoFsmIn` port) lives in system.demo and is
// substituted at parse time. The tester only needs it resolvable as a cast
// TARGET — it instantiates no peer.
extern node atomic DemoFsmGate { }

// ---- tester client node --------------------------------------------------
//
// Carries its OWN tipc address — the probe binds it as the SOURCE of the casts
// it fires at the gate. 0xd00101xx is the demo app block; pick a slot clear of
// the deployed nodes (counter..demo_gate use 0xd0010001..0xd0010007).
node atomic DemoFsmTester {
    tipc type=0xd0010101 instance=0
    ports {
        // sender on DemoFsmIn → the probe can cast DemoStart / DemoFinish /
        // DemoReset (the interface's data elements) at the gate.
        sender events provides DemoFsmIn
    }
}

// No composition / cluster: the tester is not a deployed platform process.
